    "text": "Nothing in your data suggests otherwise. Your respiratory rate is 15.8 breaths per minute overnight, close to your 30-day average of 15.2 — moves of under a breath night to night are completely normal. Two clarifications help here. Respiration is a different signal from pulse: your resting heart rate is 61 bpm, measured over the same sleep window but tracking your heart, not your lungs. And your device estimates breathing from movement and pulse patterns at medium confidence, so treat it as an estimate rather than a lab reading. The pattern that would deserve attention is a rise of a couple of breaths above your baseline holding for several nights, which often precedes illness. A single steady night like this isn't that.",
